ArticleNode - Class in com.ohnosequences.bio4j.blueprints.model.nodes.citation
The reference information for a journal citation includes the journal abbreviation, the volume number, the page range and the year of publication.

Journal names are abbreviated according to the conventions used by the National Library of Medicine (NLM) and are based on the existing ISO and ANSI standards.
